The paper discusses machine learning workflows on graphs, specifically focusing on vertex representation learning using random walks. This topic falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and network analysis and graph algorithms (cs.SI). The paper also addresses the issue of dynamic graphs, which could fall under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SD), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
